        "author_association": "MEMBER",
        "body": "So, my experience with pyarrow string types was both amazing and terrible.  \r\n\r\n## The Good\r\n\r\n- The memory impact is huge\r\n- Performance can be nicer\r\n- The GIL is dropped\r\n- It's nicely typed\r\n- The memory impact is huge\r\n\r\n## The bad\r\n\r\n-  Lots of operations don't work (or didn't)\r\n- Slices of data, when pickled, carry along the entire dataset.  This makes memory and communication performance terrible.\r\n\r\n## What to do\r\n\r\nWe should try things out and raise JIRA tickets upstream.  The Arrow folks are pretty productive these days.  We probably need to do some work and point them in the right direction.\r\n\r\ncc @cpcloud ",
